259 static void insertNoopsInBundle(MachineInstr *MI, const SIInstrInfo &TII, 0
260 unsigned Quantity) { ----
261 while (Quantity > 0) { 0
262 unsigned Arg = std::min(Quantity, 8u); 0
263 Quantity -= Arg; 0
264 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), TII.get(AMDGPU::S_NOP)) 0
265 .addImm(Arg - 1); 0
266 } ----
267 } 0

277 void GCNHazardRecognizer::processBundle() { 0
278 MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator MI = std::next(CurrCycleInstr->getIterator()); 0
279 MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator E = CurrCycleInstr->getParent()->instr_end(); 0
280 // Check bundled MachineInstr's for hazards. ----
281 for (; MI != E && MI->isInsideBundle(); ++MI) { 0
282 CurrCycleInstr = &*MI; 0
283 unsigned WaitStates = PreEmitNoopsCommon(CurrCycleInstr); 0
284 ----
285 if (IsHazardRecognizerMode) { 0
286 fixHazards(CurrCycleInstr); 0
287 ----
288 insertNoopsInBundle(CurrCycleInstr, TII, WaitStates); 0
289 } ----
290 ----
291 // It’s unnecessary to track more than MaxLookAhead instructions. Since we ----
292 // include the bundled MI directly after, only add a maximum of ----
293 // (MaxLookAhead - 1) noops to EmittedInstrs. ----
294 for (unsigned i = 0, e = std::min(WaitStates, MaxLookAhead - 1); i < e; ++i) 0
295 EmittedInstrs.push_front(nullptr); 0
296 ----
297 EmittedInstrs.push_front(CurrCycleInstr); 0
298 EmittedInstrs.resize(MaxLookAhead); 0
299 } ----
300 CurrCycleInstr = nullptr; 0
301 } 0
302 ----
303 void GCNHazardRecognizer::runOnInstruction(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
304 assert(IsHazardRecognizerMode); 0
305 ----
306 unsigned NumPreNoops = PreEmitNoops(MI); 0
307 EmitNoops(NumPreNoops); 0
308 if (MI->isInsideBundle()) 0
309 insertNoopsInBundle(MI, TII, NumPreNoops); 0
310 else ----
311 TII.insertNoops(*MI->getParent(), MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI), 0
312 NumPreNoops); ----
313 EmitInstruction(MI); 0
314 AdvanceCycle(); 0
315 } 0

317 unsigned GCNHazardRecognizer::PreEmitNoops(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
318 IsHazardRecognizerMode = true; 0
319 CurrCycleInstr = MI; 0
320 unsigned W = PreEmitNoopsCommon(MI); 0
321 fixHazards(MI); 0
322 CurrCycleInstr = nullptr; 0
323 return W; 0
324 } ----

326 unsigned GCNHazardRecognizer::PreEmitNoopsCommon(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
327 if (MI->isBundle()) 0
328 return 0; 0
329 ----
330 int WaitStates = 0; 0
331 ----
332 if (SIInstrInfo::isSMRD(*MI)) 0
333 return std::max(WaitStates, checkSMRDHazards(MI)); 0
334 ----
335 if (ST.hasNSAtoVMEMBug()) 0
336 WaitStates = std::max(WaitStates, checkNSAtoVMEMHazard(MI)); 0
337 ----
338 WaitStates = std::max(WaitStates, checkFPAtomicToDenormModeHazard(MI)); 0
339 ----
340 if (ST.hasNoDataDepHazard()) 0
341 return WaitStates; 0
342 ----
343 if (SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(*MI) || SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(*MI)) 0
344 WaitStates = std::max(WaitStates, checkVMEMHazards(MI)); 0
345 ----
346 if (SIInstrInfo::isVALU(*MI)) 0
347 WaitStates = std::max(WaitStates, checkVALUHazards(MI)); 0
348 ----
349 if (SIInstrInfo::isDPP(*MI)) 0
350 WaitStates = std::max(WaitStates, checkDPPHazards(MI)); 0
351 ----
352 if (isDivFMas(MI->getOpcode())) 0
353 WaitStates = std::max(WaitStates, checkDivFMasHazards(MI)); 0
354 ----
355 if (isRWLane(MI->getOpcode())) 0
356 WaitStates = std::max(WaitStates, checkRWLaneHazards(MI)); 0
357 ----
358 if ((SIInstrInfo::isVALU(*MI) || SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(*MI) || 0
359 SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(*MI) || SIInstrInfo::isDS(*MI) || 0
360 SIInstrInfo::isEXP(*MI)) && checkMAIVALUHazards(MI) > 0) 0
361 WaitStates = std::max(WaitStates, checkMAIVALUHazards(MI)); 0
362 ----
363 if (MI->isInlineAsm()) 0
364 return std::max(WaitStates, checkInlineAsmHazards(MI)); 0
365 ----
366 if (isSGetReg(MI->getOpcode())) 0
367 return std::max(WaitStates, checkGetRegHazards(MI)); 0
368 ----
369 if (isSSetReg(MI->getOpcode())) 0
370 return std::max(WaitStates, checkSetRegHazards(MI)); 0
371 ----
372 if (isRFE(MI->getOpcode())) 0
373 return std::max(WaitStates, checkRFEHazards(MI)); 0
374 ----
375 if ((ST.hasReadM0MovRelInterpHazard() && 0
376 (TII.isVINTRP(*MI) || isSMovRel(MI->getOpcode()) || 0
377 MI->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_ADDTID_B32 || 0
378 MI->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::DS_READ_ADDTID_B32)) || 0
379 (ST.hasReadM0SendMsgHazard() && isSendMsgTraceDataOrGDS(TII, *MI)) || 0
380 (ST.hasReadM0LdsDmaHazard() && isLdsDma(*MI)) || 0
381 (ST.hasReadM0LdsDirectHazard() && MI->readsRegister(AMDGPU::LDS_DIRECT))) 0
382 return std::max(WaitStates, checkReadM0Hazards(MI)); 0
383 ----
384 if (SIInstrInfo::isMAI(*MI)) 0
385 return std::max(WaitStates, checkMAIHazards(MI)); 0
386 ----
387 if (SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(*MI) || 0
388 SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(*MI) || 0
389 SIInstrInfo::isDS(*MI)) 0
390 return std::max(WaitStates, checkMAILdStHazards(MI)); 0
391 ----
392 return WaitStates; 0
393 } ----

396 EmittedInstrs.push_front(nullptr); 0

398 ----
399 void GCNHazardRecognizer::AdvanceCycle() { 0
400 // When the scheduler detects a stall, it will call AdvanceCycle() without ----
401 // emitting any instructions. ----
402 if (!CurrCycleInstr) { 0
403 EmittedInstrs.push_front(nullptr); 0
404 return; 0
405 } ----
406 ----
407 if (CurrCycleInstr->isBundle()) { 0
408 processBundle(); 0
409 return; 0
410 } ----
411 ----
412 unsigned NumWaitStates = TII.getNumWaitStates(*CurrCycleInstr); 0
413 if (!NumWaitStates) { 0
414 CurrCycleInstr = nullptr; 0
415 return; 0
416 } ----
417 ----
418 // Keep track of emitted instructions ----
419 EmittedInstrs.push_front(CurrCycleInstr); 0
420 ----
421 // Add a nullptr for each additional wait state after the first. Make sure ----
422 // not to add more than getMaxLookAhead() items to the list, since we ----
423 // truncate the list to that size right after this loop. ----
424 for (unsigned i = 1, e = std::min(NumWaitStates, getMaxLookAhead()); 0
425 i < e; ++i) { 0
426 EmittedInstrs.push_front(nullptr); 0
427 } ----
428 ----
429 // getMaxLookahead() is the largest number of wait states we will ever need ----
430 // to insert, so there is no point in keeping track of more than that many ----
431 // wait states. ----
432 EmittedInstrs.resize(getMaxLookAhead()); 0
433 ----
434 CurrCycleInstr = nullptr; 0
435 } ----

439 } ----

445 typedef enum { HazardFound, HazardExpired, NoHazardFound } HazardFnResult; ----

447 typedef function_ref IsExpiredFn; ----

449 ----
450 // Search for a hazard in a block and its predecessors. ----
451 template ----
452 static bool ----
453 hasHazard(StateT State, 0
454 function_ref IsHazard, ----
455 function_ref UpdateState, ----
456 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB, ----
457 MachineBasicBlock::const_reverse_instr_iterator I, ----
458 DenseSet &Visited) { ----
459 for (auto E = MBB->instr_rend(); I != E; ++I) { 0
460 // No need to look at parent BUNDLE instructions. ----
461 if (I->isBundle()) 0
462 continue; 0
463 ----
464 switch (IsHazard(State, *I)) { 0
465 case HazardFound: 0
466 return true; 0
467 case HazardExpired: 0
468 return false; 0
469 default: 0
470 // Continue search ----
471 break; 0
472 } ----
473 ----
474 if (I->isInlineAsm() || I->isMetaInstruction()) 0
475 continue; 0
476 ----
477 UpdateState(State, *I); 0
478 } ----
479 ----
480 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
481 if (!Visited.insert(Pred).second) 0
482 continue; 0
483 ----
484 if (hasHazard(State, IsHazard, UpdateState, Pred, Pred->instr_rbegin(), 0
485 Visited)) ----
486 return true; 0
487 } ----
488 ----
489 return false; 0
490 } ----
491 ----
492 // Returns a minimum wait states since \p I walking all predecessors. ----
493 // Only scans until \p IsExpired does not return true. ----
494 // Can only be run in a hazard recognizer mode. ----
495 static int getWaitStatesSince( 0
496 GCNHazardRecognizer::IsHazardFn IsHazard, const MachineBasicBlock *MBB, ----
497 MachineBasicBlock::const_reverse_instr_iterator I, int WaitStates, ----
498 IsExpiredFn IsExpired, DenseSet &Visited, ----
499 GetNumWaitStatesFn GetNumWaitStates = SIInstrInfo::getNumWaitStates) { ----
500 for (auto E = MBB->instr_rend(); I != E; ++I) { 0
501 // Don't add WaitStates for parent BUNDLE instructions. ----
502 if (I->isBundle()) 0
503 continue; 0
504 ----
505 if (IsHazard(*I)) 0
506 return WaitStates; 0
507 ----
508 if (I->isInlineAsm()) 0
509 continue; 0
510 ----
511 WaitStates += GetNumWaitStates(*I); 0
512 ----
513 if (IsExpired(*I, WaitStates)) 0
514 return std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
515 } ----
516 ----
517 int MinWaitStates = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
518 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
519 if (!Visited.insert(Pred).second) 0
520 continue; 0
521 ----
522 int W = getWaitStatesSince(IsHazard, Pred, Pred->instr_rbegin(), WaitStates, 0
523 IsExpired, Visited, GetNumWaitStates); 0
524 ----
525 MinWaitStates = std::min(MinWaitStates, W); 0
526 } ----
527 ----
528 return MinWaitStates; 0
529 } ----
530 ----
531 static int getWaitStatesSince(GCNHazardRecognizer::IsHazardFn IsHazard, 0
532 const MachineInstr *MI, IsExpiredFn IsExpired) { ----
533 DenseSet Visited; 0
534 return getWaitStatesSince(IsHazard, MI->getParent(), 0
535 std::next(MI->getReverseIterator()), ----
536 0, IsExpired, Visited); 0
537 } 0
538 ----
539 int GCNHazardRecognizer::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn IsHazard, int Limit) { 0
540 if (IsHazardRecognizerMode) { 0
541 auto IsExpiredFn = [Limit](const MachineInstr &, int WaitStates) { 0
542 return WaitStates >= Limit; 0
543 }; 0
544 return ::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazard, CurrCycleInstr, IsExpiredFn); 0
545 } ----
546 ----
547 int WaitStates = 0; 0
548 for (MachineInstr *MI : EmittedInstrs) { 0
549 if (MI) { 0
550 if (IsHazard(*MI)) 0
551 return WaitStates; 0
552 ----
553 if (MI->isInlineAsm()) 0
554 continue; 0
555 } ----
556 ++WaitStates; 0
557 ----
558 if (WaitStates >= Limit) 0
559 break; 0
560 } ----
561 return std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
562 } ----

608 static bool breaksSMEMSoftClause(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
609 return !SIInstrInfo::isSMRD(*MI); 0

612 static bool breaksVMEMSoftClause(MachineInstr *MI) { 0

615 ----
616 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkSoftClauseHazards(MachineInstr *MEM) { 0
617 // SMEM soft clause are only present on VI+, and only matter if xnack is ----
618 // enabled. ----
619 if (!ST.isXNACKEnabled()) 0
620 return 0; 0
621 ----
622 bool IsSMRD = TII.isSMRD(*MEM); 0
623 ----
624 resetClause(); 0
625 ----
626 // A soft-clause is any group of consecutive SMEM instructions. The ----
627 // instructions in this group may return out of order and/or may be ----
628 // replayed (i.e. the same instruction issued more than once). ----
629 // ----
630 // In order to handle these situations correctly we need to make sure that ----
631 // when a clause has more than one instruction, no instruction in the clause ----
632 // writes to a register that is read by another instruction in the clause ----
633 // (including itself). If we encounter this situation, we need to break the ----
634 // clause by inserting a non SMEM instruction. ----
635 ----
636 for (MachineInstr *MI : EmittedInstrs) { 0
637 // When we hit a non-SMEM instruction then we have passed the start of the ----
638 // clause and we can stop. ----
639 if (!MI) 0
640 break; 0
641 ----
642 if (IsSMRD ? breaksSMEMSoftClause(MI) : breaksVMEMSoftClause(MI)) 0
643 break; 0
644 ----
645 addClauseInst(*MI); 0
646 } ----
647 ----
648 if (ClauseDefs.none()) 0
649 return 0; 0
650 ----
651 // We need to make sure not to put loads and stores in the same clause if they ----
652 // use the same address. For now, just start a new clause whenever we see a ----
653 // store. ----
654 if (MEM->mayStore()) 0
655 return 1; 0
656 ----
657 addClauseInst(*MEM); 0
658 ----
659 // If the set of defs and uses intersect then we cannot add this instruction ----
660 // to the clause, so we have a hazard. ----
661 return ClauseDefs.anyCommon(ClauseUses) ? 1 : 0; 0
662 } ----
663 ----
664 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkSMRDHazards(MachineInstr *SMRD) { 0
665 int WaitStatesNeeded = 0; 0
666 ----
667 WaitStatesNeeded = checkSoftClauseHazards(SMRD); 0
668 ----
669 // This SMRD hazard only affects SI. ----
670 if (!ST.hasSMRDReadVALUDefHazard()) 0
671 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
672 ----
673 // A read of an SGPR by SMRD instruction requires 4 wait states when the ----
674 // SGPR was written by a VALU instruction. ----
675 int SmrdSgprWaitStates = 4; 0
676 auto IsHazardDefFn = [this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
677 return TII.isVALU(MI); 0
678 }; 0
679 auto IsBufferHazardDefFn = [this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
680 return TII.isSALU(MI); 0
681 }; 0
682 ----
683 bool IsBufferSMRD = TII.isBufferSMRD(*SMRD); 0
684 ----
685 for (const MachineOperand &Use : SMRD->uses()) { 0
686 if (!Use.isReg()) 0
687 continue; 0
688 int WaitStatesNeededForUse = ----
689 SmrdSgprWaitStates - getWaitStatesSinceDef(Use.getReg(), IsHazardDefFn, 0
690 SmrdSgprWaitStates); 0
691 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
692 ----
693 // This fixes what appears to be undocumented hardware behavior in SI where ----
694 // s_mov writing a descriptor and s_buffer_load_dword reading the descriptor ----
695 // needs some number of nops in between. We don't know how many we need, but ----
696 // let's use 4. This wasn't discovered before probably because the only ----
697 // case when this happens is when we expand a 64-bit pointer into a full ----
698 // descriptor and use s_buffer_load_dword instead of s_load_dword, which was ----
699 // probably never encountered in the closed-source land. ----
700 if (IsBufferSMRD) { 0
701 int WaitStatesNeededForUse = ----
702 SmrdSgprWaitStates - getWaitStatesSinceDef(Use.getReg(), 0
703 IsBufferHazardDefFn, ----
704 SmrdSgprWaitStates); 0
705 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
706 } ----
707 } ----
708 ----
709 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
710 } ----
711 ----
712 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkVMEMHazards(MachineInstr* VMEM) { 0
713 if (!ST.hasVMEMReadSGPRVALUDefHazard()) 0
714 return 0; 0
715 ----
716 int WaitStatesNeeded = checkSoftClauseHazards(VMEM); 0
717 ----
718 // A read of an SGPR by a VMEM instruction requires 5 wait states when the ----
719 // SGPR was written by a VALU Instruction. ----
720 const int VmemSgprWaitStates = 5; 0
721 auto IsHazardDefFn = [this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
722 return TII.isVALU(MI); 0
723 }; 0
724 for (const MachineOperand &Use : VMEM->uses()) { 0
725 if (!Use.isReg() || TRI.isVectorRegister(MF.getRegInfo(), Use.getReg())) 0
726 continue; 0
727 ----
728 int WaitStatesNeededForUse = ----
729 VmemSgprWaitStates - getWaitStatesSinceDef(Use.getReg(), IsHazardDefFn, 0
730 VmemSgprWaitStates); 0
731 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
732 } ----
733 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
734 } ----
735 ----
736 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkDPPHazards(MachineInstr *DPP) { 0
737 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
738 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
739 ----
740 // Check for DPP VGPR read after VALU VGPR write and EXEC write. ----
741 int DppVgprWaitStates = 2; 0
742 int DppExecWaitStates = 5; 0
743 int WaitStatesNeeded = 0; 0
744 auto IsHazardDefFn = [TII](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
745 return TII->isVALU(MI); 0
746 }; 0
747 ----
748 for (const MachineOperand &Use : DPP->uses()) { 0
749 if (!Use.isReg() || !TRI->isVGPR(MF.getRegInfo(), Use.getReg())) 0
750 continue; 0
751 int WaitStatesNeededForUse = ----
752 DppVgprWaitStates - getWaitStatesSinceDef( 0
753 Use.getReg(), 0
754 [](const MachineInstr &) { return true; }, 0
755 DppVgprWaitStates); 0
756 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
757 } ----
758 ----
759 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max( 0
760 WaitStatesNeeded, ----
761 DppExecWaitStates - getWaitStatesSinceDef(AMDGPU::EXEC, IsHazardDefFn, 0
762 DppExecWaitStates)); ----
763 ----
764 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
765 } ----

768 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0

770 // v_div_fmas requires 4 wait states after a write to vcc from a VALU ----
771 // instruction. ----
772 const int DivFMasWaitStates = 4; 0

774 return TII->isVALU(MI); 0
775 }; 0
776 int WaitStatesNeeded = getWaitStatesSinceDef(AMDGPU::VCC, IsHazardDefFn, 0

780 } ----

806 ----
807 int GCNHazardRecognizer::createsVALUHazard(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
808 if (!MI.mayStore()) 0
809 return -1; 0
810 ----
811 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
812 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
813 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MI.getDesc(); 0
814 ----
815 int VDataIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
816 int VDataRCID = -1; 0
817 if (VDataIdx != -1) 0
818 VDataRCID = Desc.operands()[VDataIdx].RegClass; 0
819 ----
820 if (TII->isMUBUF(MI) || TII->isMTBUF(MI)) { 0
821 // There is no hazard if the instruction does not use vector regs ----
822 // (like wbinvl1) ----
823 if (VDataIdx == -1) 0
824 return -1; 0
825 // For MUBUF/MTBUF instructions this hazard only exists if the ----
826 // instruction is not using a register in the soffset field. ----
827 const MachineOperand *SOffset = ----
828 TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::soffset); 0
829 // If we have no soffset operand, then assume this field has been ----
830 // hardcoded to zero. ----
831 if (AMDGPU::getRegBitWidth(VDataRCID) > 64 && 0
832 (!SOffset || !SOffset->isReg())) 0
833 return VDataIdx; 0
834 } ----
835 ----
836 // MIMG instructions create a hazard if they don't use a 256-bit T# and ----
837 // the store size is greater than 8 bytes and they have more than two bits ----
838 // of their dmask set. ----
839 // All our MIMG definitions use a 256-bit T#, so we can skip checking for them. ----
840 if (TII->isMIMG(MI)) { 0
841 int SRsrcIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc); 0
842 assert(SRsrcIdx != -1 && 0
843 AMDGPU::getRegBitWidth(Desc.operands()[SRsrcIdx].RegClass) == 256); ----
844 (void)SRsrcIdx; ----
845 } ----
846 ----
847 if (TII->isFLAT(MI)) { 0
848 int DataIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
849 if (AMDGPU::getRegBitWidth(Desc.operands()[DataIdx].RegClass) > 64) 0
850 return DataIdx; 0
851 } ----
852 ----
853 return -1; 0
854 } ----
855 ----
856 int ----
857 GCNHazardRecognizer::checkVALUHazardsHelper(const MachineOperand &Def, 0
858 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
859 // Helper to check for the hazard where VMEM instructions that store more than ----
860 // 8 bytes can have there store data over written by the next instruction. ----
861 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
862 ----
863 const int VALUWaitStates = ST.hasGFX940Insts() ? 2 : 1; 0
864 int WaitStatesNeeded = 0; 0
865 ----
866 if (!TRI->isVectorRegister(MRI, Def.getReg())) 0
867 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
868 Register Reg = Def.getReg(); 0
869 auto IsHazardFn = [this, Reg, TRI](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
870 int DataIdx = createsVALUHazard(MI); 0
871 return DataIdx >= 0 && 0
872 TRI->regsOverlap(MI.getOperand(DataIdx).getReg(), Reg); 0
873 }; 0
874 int WaitStatesNeededForDef = ----
875 VALUWaitStates - getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, VALUWaitStates); 0
876 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForDef); 0
877 ----
878 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
879 } ----
880 ----
881 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkVALUHazards(MachineInstr *VALU) { 0
882 int WaitStatesNeeded = 0; 0
883 ----
884 if (ST.hasTransForwardingHazard() && !SIInstrInfo::isTRANS(*VALU)) { 0
885 const int TransDefWaitstates = 1; 0
886 ----
887 auto IsTransDefFn = [this, VALU](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
888 if (!SIInstrInfo::isTRANS(MI)) 0
889 return false; 0
890 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
891 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
892 Register Def = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst)->getReg(); 0
893 ----
894 for (const MachineOperand &Use : VALU->explicit_uses()) { 0
895 if (Use.isReg() && TRI->regsOverlap(Def, Use.getReg())) 0
896 return true; 0
897 } ----
898 ----
899 return false; 0
900 }; 0
901 ----
902 int WaitStatesNeededForDef = ----
903 TransDefWaitstates - 0
904 getWaitStatesSince(IsTransDefFn, TransDefWaitstates); 0
905 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForDef); 0
906 } ----
907 ----
908 if (ST.hasDstSelForwardingHazard()) { 0
909 const int Shift16DefWaitstates = 1; 0
910 ----
911 auto IsShift16BitDefFn = [this, VALU](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
912 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI)) 0
913 return false; 0
914 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
915 if (SIInstrInfo::isSDWA(MI)) { 0
916 if (auto *DstSel = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::dst_sel)) 0
917 if (DstSel->getImm() == AMDGPU::SDWA::DWORD) 0
918 return false; 0
919 } else { ----
920 if (!AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(MI.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel) || 0
921 !(TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src0_modifiers) ----
922 ->getImm() & 0
923 SISrcMods::DST_OP_SEL)) ----
924 return false; 0
925 } ----
926 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
927 if (auto *Dst = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst)) { 0
928 Register Def = Dst->getReg(); 0
929 ----
930 for (const MachineOperand &Use : VALU->explicit_uses()) { 0
931 if (Use.isReg() && TRI->regsOverlap(Def, Use.getReg())) 0
932 return true; 0
933 } ----
934 } ----
935 ----
936 return false; 0
937 }; 0
938 ----
939 int WaitStatesNeededForDef = ----
940 Shift16DefWaitstates - 0
941 getWaitStatesSince(IsShift16BitDefFn, Shift16DefWaitstates); 0
942 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForDef); 0
943 } ----
944 ----
945 if (ST.hasVDecCoExecHazard()) { 0
946 const int VALUWriteSGPRVALUReadWaitstates = 2; 0
947 const int VALUWriteEXECRWLane = 4; 0
948 const int VALUWriteVGPRReadlaneRead = 1; 0
949 ----
950 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
951 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
952 Register UseReg; 0
953 auto IsVALUDefSGPRFn = [&UseReg, TRI](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
954 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI)) 0
955 return false; 0
956 return MI.modifiesRegister(UseReg, TRI); 0
957 }; 0
958 ----
959 for (const MachineOperand &Use : VALU->explicit_uses()) { 0
960 if (!Use.isReg()) 0
961 continue; 0
962 ----
963 UseReg = Use.getReg(); 0
964 if (TRI->isSGPRReg(MRI, UseReg)) { 0
965 int WaitStatesNeededForDef = ----
966 VALUWriteSGPRVALUReadWaitstates - 0
967 getWaitStatesSince(IsVALUDefSGPRFn, 0
968 VALUWriteSGPRVALUReadWaitstates); 0
969 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForDef); 0
970 } ----
971 } ----
972 ----
973 if (VALU->readsRegister(AMDGPU::VCC, TRI)) { 0
974 UseReg = AMDGPU::VCC; 0
975 int WaitStatesNeededForDef = ----
976 VALUWriteSGPRVALUReadWaitstates - 0
977 getWaitStatesSince(IsVALUDefSGPRFn, VALUWriteSGPRVALUReadWaitstates); 0
978 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForDef); 0
979 } ----
980 ----
981 switch (VALU->getOpcode()) { 0
982 case AMDGPU::V_READLANE_B32: 0
983 case AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32: { ----
984 MachineOperand *Src = TII.getNamedOperand(*VALU, AMDGPU::OpName::src0); 0
985 UseReg = Src->getReg(); 0
986 int WaitStatesNeededForDef = ----
987 VALUWriteVGPRReadlaneRead - 0
988 getWaitStatesSince(IsVALUDefSGPRFn, VALUWriteVGPRReadlaneRead); 0
989 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForDef); 0
990 } ----
991 [[fallthrough]]; ----
992 case AMDGPU::V_WRITELANE_B32: { 0
993 UseReg = AMDGPU::EXEC; 0
994 int WaitStatesNeededForDef = ----
995 VALUWriteEXECRWLane - 0
996 getWaitStatesSince(IsVALUDefSGPRFn, VALUWriteEXECRWLane); 0
997 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForDef); 0
998 break; 0
999 } ----
1000 default: 0
1001 break; 0
1002 } ----
1003 } ----
1004 ----
1005 // This checks for the hazard where VMEM instructions that store more than ----
1006 // 8 bytes can have there store data over written by the next instruction. ----
1007 if (!ST.has12DWordStoreHazard()) 0
1008 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
1009 ----
1010 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1011 ----
1012 for (const MachineOperand &Def : VALU->defs()) { 0
1013 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, checkVALUHazardsHelper(Def, MRI)); 0
1014 } ----
1015 ----
1016 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
1017 } ----
1018 ----
1019 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkInlineAsmHazards(MachineInstr *IA) { 0
1020 // This checks for hazards associated with inline asm statements. ----
1021 // Since inline asms can contain just about anything, we use this ----
1022 // to call/leverage other check*Hazard routines. Note that ----
1023 // this function doesn't attempt to address all possible inline asm ----
1024 // hazards (good luck), but is a collection of what has been ----
1025 // problematic thus far. ----
1026 ----
1027 // see checkVALUHazards() ----
1028 if (!ST.has12DWordStoreHazard()) 0
1029 return 0; 0
1030 ----
1031 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1032 int WaitStatesNeeded = 0; 0
1033 ----
1034 for (const MachineOperand &Op : 0
1035 llvm::drop_begin(IA->operands(), InlineAsm::MIOp_FirstOperand)) { 0
1036 if (Op.isReg() && Op.isDef()) { 0
1037 WaitStatesNeeded = 0
1038 std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, checkVALUHazardsHelper(Op, MRI)); 0
1039 } ----
1040 } ----
1041 ----
1042 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
1043 } ----

1048 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0

1088 void GCNHazardRecognizer::fixHazards(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1089 fixVMEMtoScalarWriteHazards(MI); 0

1092 fixVcmpxExecWARHazard(MI); 0

1094 if (ST.hasLdsDirect()) { 0
1095 fixLdsDirectVALUHazard(MI); 0
1096 fixLdsDirectVMEMHazard(MI); 0
1097 } ----
1098 fixVALUPartialForwardingHazard(MI); 0

1100 fixWMMAHazards(MI); 0
1101 fixShift64HighRegBug(MI); 0
1102 fixVALUMaskWriteHazard(MI); 0

1104 ----
1105 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixVcmpxPermlaneHazards(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1106 if (!ST.hasVcmpxPermlaneHazard() || !isPermlane(*MI)) 0
1107 return false; 0
1108 ----
1109 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
1110 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1111 auto IsHazardFn = [TII, TRI](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1112 return (TII->isVOPC(MI) || 0
1113 ((TII->isVOP3(MI) || TII->isSDWA(MI)) && MI.isCompare())) && 0
1114 MI.modifiesRegister(AMDGPU::EXEC, TRI); 0
1115 }; 0
1116 ----
1117 auto IsExpiredFn = [](const MachineInstr &MI, int) { 0
1118 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1119 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI) && Opc != AMDGPU::V_NOP_e32 && 0
1120 Opc != AMDGPU::V_NOP_e64 && Opc != AMDGPU::V_NOP_sdwa; 0
1121 }; ----
1122 ----
1123 if (::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn) == 0
1124 std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1125 return false; 0
1126 ----
1127 // V_NOP will be discarded by SQ. ----
1128 // Use V_MOV_B32 v?, v?. Register must be alive so use src0 of V_PERMLANE* ----
1129 // which is always a VGPR and available. ----
1130 auto *Src0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src0); 0
1131 Register Reg = Src0->getReg(); 0
1132 bool IsUndef = Src0->isUndef(); 0
1133 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1134 TII->get(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32)) ----
1135 .addReg(Reg, RegState::Define | (IsUndef ? RegState::Dead : 0)) 0
1136 .addReg(Reg, IsUndef ? RegState::Undef : RegState::Kill); 0
1137 ----
1138 return true; 0
1139 } ----
1140 ----
1141 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixVMEMtoScalarWriteHazards(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1142 if (!ST.hasVMEMtoScalarWriteHazard()) 0
1143 return false; 0
1144 ----
1145 if (!SIInstrInfo::isSALU(*MI) && !SIInstrInfo::isSMRD(*MI)) 0
1146 return false; 0
1147 ----
1148 if (MI->getNumDefs() == 0) 0
1149 return false; 0
1150 ----
1151 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1152 ----
1153 auto IsHazardFn = [TRI, MI](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1154 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(I) && !SIInstrInfo::isDS(I) && 0
1155 !SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(I)) 0
1156 return false; 0
1157 ----
1158 for (const MachineOperand &Def : MI->defs()) { 0
1159 const MachineOperand *Op = ----
1160 I.findRegisterUseOperand(Def.getReg(), false, TRI); 0
1161 if (!Op) 0
1162 continue; 0
1163 return true; 0
1164 } ----
1165 return false; 0
1166 }; 0
1167 ----
1168 auto IsExpiredFn = [](const MachineInstr &MI, int) { 0
1169 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI) || 0
1170 (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT && 0
1171 !MI.getOperand(0).getImm()) || 0
1172 (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR && 0
1173 AMDGPU::DepCtr::decodeFieldVmVsrc(MI.getOperand(0).getImm()) == 0); 0
1174 }; ----
1175 ----
1176 if (::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn) == 0
1177 std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1178 return false; 0
1179 ----
1180 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
1181 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1182 TII->get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR)) ----
1183 .addImm(AMDGPU::DepCtr::encodeFieldVmVsrc(0)); 0
1184 return true; 0
1185 } ----
1186 ----
1187 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixSMEMtoVectorWriteHazards(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1188 if (!ST.hasSMEMtoVectorWriteHazard()) 0
1189 return false; 0
1190 ----
1191 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVALU(*MI)) 0
1192 return false; 0
1193 ----
1194 unsigned SDSTName; ----
1195 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
1196 case AMDGPU::V_READLANE_B32: 0
1197 case AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32: ----
1198 SDSTName = AMDGPU::OpName::vdst; 0
1199 break; 0
1200 default: 0
1201 SDSTName = AMDGPU::OpName::sdst; 0
1202 break; 0
1203 } ----
1204 ----
1205 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
1206 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1207 const AMDGPU::IsaVersion IV = AMDGPU::getIsaVersion(ST.getCPU()); 0
1208 const MachineOperand *SDST = TII->getNamedOperand(*MI, SDSTName); 0
1209 if (!SDST) { 0
1210 for (const auto &MO : MI->implicit_operands()) { 0
1211 if (MO.isDef() && TRI->isSGPRClass(TRI->getPhysRegBaseClass(MO.getReg()))) { 0
1212 SDST = &MO; 0
1213 break; 0
1214 } ----
1215 } ----
1216 } ----
1217 ----
1218 if (!SDST) 0
1219 return false; 0
1220 ----
1221 const Register SDSTReg = SDST->getReg(); 0
1222 auto IsHazardFn = [SDSTReg, TRI](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1223 return SIInstrInfo::isSMRD(I) && I.readsRegister(SDSTReg, TRI); 0
1224 }; 0
1225 ----
1226 auto IsExpiredFn = [TII, IV](const MachineInstr &MI, int) { 0
1227 if (TII->isSALU(MI)) { 0
1228 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
1229 case AMDGPU::S_SETVSKIP: 0
1230 case AMDGPU::S_VERSION: ----
1231 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_VSCNT: ----
1232 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_VMCNT: ----
1233 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_EXPCNT: ----
1234 // These instructions cannot not mitigate the hazard. ----
1235 return false; 0
1236 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_LGKMCNT: 0
1237 // Reducing lgkmcnt count to 0 always mitigates the hazard. ----
1238 return (MI.getOperand(1).getImm() == 0) && 0
1239 (MI.getOperand(0).getReg() == AMDGPU::SGPR_NULL); 0
1240 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT: { 0
1241 const int64_t Imm = MI.getOperand(0).getImm(); 0
1242 AMDGPU::Waitcnt Decoded = AMDGPU::decodeWaitcnt(IV, Imm); 0
1243 return (Decoded.LgkmCnt == 0); 0
1244 } ----
1245 default: 0
1246 // SOPP instructions cannot mitigate the hazard. ----
1247 if (TII->isSOPP(MI)) 0
1248 return false; 0
1249 // At this point the SALU can be assumed to mitigate the hazard ----
1250 // because either: ----
1251 // (a) it is independent of the at risk SMEM (breaking chain), ----
1252 // or ----
1253 // (b) it is dependent on the SMEM, in which case an appropriate ----
1254 // s_waitcnt lgkmcnt _must_ exist between it and the at risk ----
1255 // SMEM instruction. ----
1256 return true; 0
1257 } ----
1258 } ----
1259 return false; 0
1260 }; 0
1261 ----
1262 if (::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn) == 0
1263 std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1264 return false; 0
1265 ----
1266 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1267 TII->get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32), AMDGPU::SGPR_NULL) ----
1268 .addImm(0); 0
1269 return true; 0
1270 } ----
1271 ----
1272 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixVcmpxExecWARHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1273 if (!ST.hasVcmpxExecWARHazard() || !SIInstrInfo::isVALU(*MI)) 0
1274 return false; 0
1275 ----
1276 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1277 if (!MI->modifiesRegister(AMDGPU::EXEC, TRI)) 0
1278 return false; 0
1279 ----
1280 auto IsHazardFn = [TRI](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1281 if (SIInstrInfo::isVALU(I)) 0
1282 return false; 0
1283 return I.readsRegister(AMDGPU::EXEC, TRI); 0
1284 }; 0
1285 ----
1286 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
1287 auto IsExpiredFn = [TII, TRI](const MachineInstr &MI, int) { 0
1288 if (SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI)) { 0
1289 if (TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::sdst)) 0
1290 return true; 0
1291 for (auto MO : MI.implicit_operands()) 0
1292 if (MO.isDef() && TRI->isSGPRClass(TRI->getPhysRegBaseClass(MO.getReg()))) 0
1293 return true; 0
1294 } ----
1295 if (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR && 0
1296 AMDGPU::DepCtr::decodeFieldSaSdst(MI.getOperand(0).getImm()) == 0) 0
1297 return true; 0
1298 return false; 0
1299 }; 0
1300 ----
1301 if (::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn) == 0
1302 std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1303 return false; 0
1304 ----
1305 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1306 TII->get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR)) ----
1307 .addImm(AMDGPU::DepCtr::encodeFieldSaSdst(0)); 0
1308 return true; 0
1309 } ----
1310 ----
1311 static bool shouldRunLdsBranchVmemWARHazardFixup(const MachineFunction &MF, 0
1312 const GCNSubtarget &ST) { ----
1313 if (!ST.hasLdsBranchVmemWARHazard()) 0
1314 return false; 0
1315 ----
1316 // Check if the necessary condition for the hazard is met: both LDS and VMEM ----
1317 // instructions need to appear in the same function. ----
1318 bool HasLds = false; 0
1319 bool HasVmem = false; 0
1320 for (auto &MBB : MF) { 0
1321 for (auto &MI : MBB) { 0
1322 HasLds |= SIInstrInfo::isDS(MI); 0
1323 HasVmem |= 0
1324 SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(MI) || SIInstrInfo::isSegmentSpecificFLAT(MI); 0
1325 if (HasLds && HasVmem) 0
1326 return true; 0
1327 } ----
1328 } ----
1329 return false; 0
1330 } ----
1331 ----
1332 static bool isStoreCountWaitZero(const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1333 return I.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_VSCNT && 0
1334 I.getOperand(0).getReg() == AMDGPU::SGPR_NULL && 0
1335 !I.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
1336 } ----
1337 ----
1338 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixLdsBranchVmemWARHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1339 if (!RunLdsBranchVmemWARHazardFixup) 0
1340 return false; 0
1341 ----
1342 assert(ST.hasLdsBranchVmemWARHazard()); 0
1343 ----
1344 auto IsHazardInst = [](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1345 if (SIInstrInfo::isDS(MI)) 0
1346 return 1; 0
1347 if (SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(MI) || SIInstrInfo::isSegmentSpecificFLAT(MI)) 0
1348 return 2; 0
1349 return 0; 0
1350 }; ----
1351 ----
1352 auto InstType = IsHazardInst(*MI); 0
1353 if (!InstType) 0
1354 return false; 0
1355 ----
1356 auto IsExpiredFn = [&IsHazardInst](const MachineInstr &I, int) { 0
1357 return IsHazardInst(I) || isStoreCountWaitZero(I); 0
1358 }; 0
1359 ----
1360 auto IsHazardFn = [InstType, &IsHazardInst](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1361 if (!I.isBranch()) 0
1362 return false; 0
1363 ----
1364 auto IsHazardFn = [InstType, IsHazardInst](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1365 auto InstType2 = IsHazardInst(I); 0
1366 return InstType2 && InstType != InstType2; 0
1367 }; 0
1368 ----
1369 auto IsExpiredFn = [InstType, &IsHazardInst](const MachineInstr &I, int) { 0
1370 auto InstType2 = IsHazardInst(I); 0
1371 if (InstType == InstType2) 0
1372 return true; 0
1373 ----
1374 return isStoreCountWaitZero(I); 0
1375 }; 0
1376 ----
1377 return ::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, &I, IsExpiredFn) != 0
1378 std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
1379 }; 0
1380 ----
1381 if (::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn) == 0
1382 std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1383 return false; 0
1384 ----
1385 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
1386 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1387 TII->get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_VSCNT)) ----
1388 .addReg(AMDGPU::SGPR_NULL, RegState::Undef) 0
1389 .addImm(0); 0
1390 ----
1391 return true; 0
1392 } ----
1393 ----
1394 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixLdsDirectVALUHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1395 if (!SIInstrInfo::isLDSDIR(*MI)) 0
1396 return false; 0
1397 ----
1398 const int NoHazardWaitStates = 15; 0
1399 const MachineOperand *VDST = TII.getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst); 0
1400 const Register VDSTReg = VDST->getReg(); 0
1401 ----
1402 bool VisitedTrans = false; 0
1403 auto IsHazardFn = [this, VDSTReg, &VisitedTrans](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1404 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVALU(I)) 0
1405 return false; 0
1406 VisitedTrans = VisitedTrans || SIInstrInfo::isTRANS(I); 0
1407 // Cover both WAR and WAW ----
1408 return I.readsRegister(VDSTReg, &TRI) || I.modifiesRegister(VDSTReg, &TRI); 0
1409 }; 0
1410 auto IsExpiredFn = [&](const MachineInstr &I, int WaitStates) { 0
1411 if (WaitStates >= NoHazardWaitStates) 0
1412 return true; 0
1413 // Instructions which cause va_vdst==0 expire hazard ----
1414 return SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(I) || SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(I) || 0
1415 SIInstrInfo::isDS(I) || SIInstrInfo::isEXP(I); 0
1416 }; ----
1417 auto GetWaitStatesFn = [](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1418 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI) ? 1 : 0; 0
1419 }; ----
1420 ----
1421 DenseSet Visited; 0
1422 auto Count = ::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI->getParent(), 0
1423 std::next(MI->getReverseIterator()), 0, 0
1424 IsExpiredFn, Visited, GetWaitStatesFn); 0
1425 ----
1426 // Transcendentals can execute in parallel to other VALUs. ----
1427 // This makes va_vdst count unusable with a mixture of VALU and TRANS. ----
1428 if (VisitedTrans) 0
1429 Count = 0; 0
1430 ----
1431 MachineOperand *WaitVdstOp = ----
1432 TII.getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::waitvdst); 0
1433 WaitVdstOp->setImm(std::min(Count, NoHazardWaitStates)); 0
1434 ----
1435 return true; 0
1436 } 0
1437 ----
1438 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixLdsDirectVMEMHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1439 if (!SIInstrInfo::isLDSDIR(*MI)) 0
1440 return false; 0
1441 ----
1442 const MachineOperand *VDST = TII.getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst); 0
1443 const Register VDSTReg = VDST->getReg(); 0
1444 ----
1445 auto IsHazardFn = [this, VDSTReg](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1446 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(I) && !SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(I) && 0
1447 !SIInstrInfo::isDS(I)) 0
1448 return false; 0
1449 return I.readsRegister(VDSTReg, &TRI) || I.modifiesRegister(VDSTReg, &TRI); 0
1450 }; 0
1451 auto IsExpiredFn = [](const MachineInstr &I, int) { 0
1452 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(I) || SIInstrInfo::isEXP(I) || 0
1453 (I.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT && !I.getOperand(0).getImm()) || 0
1454 (I.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR && 0
1455 AMDGPU::DepCtr::decodeFieldVmVsrc(I.getOperand(0).getImm()) == 0); 0
1456 }; ----
1457 ----
1458 if (::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn) == 0
1459 std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1460 return false; 0
1461 ----
1462 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1463 TII.get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR)) 0
1464 .addImm(AMDGPU::DepCtr::encodeFieldVmVsrc(0)); 0
1465 ----
1466 return true; 0
1467 } ----
1468 ----
1469 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixVALUPartialForwardingHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1470 if (!ST.isWave64()) 0
1471 return false; 0
1472 if (!ST.hasVALUPartialForwardingHazard()) 0
1473 return false; 0
1474 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVALU(*MI)) 0
1475 return false; 0
1476 ----
1477 SmallSetVector SrcVGPRs; 0
1478 ----
1479 for (const MachineOperand &Use : MI->explicit_uses()) { 0
1480 if (Use.isReg() && TRI.isVGPR(MF.getRegInfo(), Use.getReg())) 0
1481 SrcVGPRs.insert(Use.getReg()); 0
1482 } ----
1483 ----
1484 // Only applies with >= 2 unique VGPR sources ----
1485 if (SrcVGPRs.size() <= 1) 0
1486 return false; 0
1487 ----
1488 // Look for the following pattern: ----
1489 // Va <- VALU [PreExecPos] ----
1490 // intv1 ----
1491 // Exec <- SALU [ExecPos] ----
1492 // intv2 ----
1493 // Vb <- VALU [PostExecPos] ----
1494 // intv3 ----
1495 // MI Va, Vb (WaitState = 0) ----
1496 // ----
1497 // Where: ----
1498 // intv1 + intv2 <= 2 VALUs ----
1499 // intv3 <= 4 VALUs ----
1500 // ----
1501 // If found, insert an appropriate S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR before MI. ----
1502 ----
1503 const int Intv1plus2MaxVALUs = 2; 0
1504 const int Intv3MaxVALUs = 4; 0
1505 const int IntvMaxVALUs = 6; 0
1506 const int NoHazardVALUWaitStates = IntvMaxVALUs + 2; 0
1507 ----
1508 struct StateType { ----
1509 SmallDenseMap DefPos; ----
1510 int ExecPos = std::numeric_limits::max(); ----
1511 int VALUs = 0; ----
1512 }; ----
1513 ----
1514 StateType State; 0
1515 ----
1516 // This overloads expiry testing with all the hazard detection ----
1517 auto IsHazardFn = [&, this](StateType &State, const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1518 // Too many VALU states have passed ----
1519 if (State.VALUs > NoHazardVALUWaitStates) 0
1520 return HazardExpired; 0
1521 ----
1522 // Instructions which cause va_vdst==0 expire hazard ----
1523 if (SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(I) || SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(I) || 0
1524 SIInstrInfo::isDS(I) || SIInstrInfo::isEXP(I) || 0
1525 (I.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR && 0
1526 AMDGPU::DepCtr::decodeFieldVaVdst(I.getOperand(0).getImm()) == 0)) 0
1527 return HazardExpired; 0
1528 ----
1529 // Track registers writes ----
1530 bool Changed = false; 0
1531 if (SIInstrInfo::isVALU(I)) { 0
1532 for (Register Src : SrcVGPRs) { 0
1533 if (!State.DefPos.count(Src) && I.modifiesRegister(Src, &TRI)) { 0
1534 State.DefPos[Src] = State.VALUs; 0
1535 Changed = true; 0
1536 } ----
1537 } ----
1538 } else if (SIInstrInfo::isSALU(I)) { 0
1539 if (State.ExecPos == std::numeric_limits::max()) { 0
1540 if (!State.DefPos.empty() && I.modifiesRegister(AMDGPU::EXEC, &TRI)) { 0
1541 State.ExecPos = State.VALUs; 0
1542 Changed = true; 0
1543 } ----
1544 } ----
1545 } ----
1546 ----
1547 // Early expiration: too many VALUs in intv3 ----
1548 if (State.VALUs > Intv3MaxVALUs && State.DefPos.empty()) 0
1549 return HazardExpired; 0
1550 ----
1551 // Only evaluate state if something changed ----
1552 if (!Changed) 0
1553 return NoHazardFound; 0
1554 ----
1555 // Determine positions of VALUs pre/post exec change ----
1556 if (State.ExecPos == std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1557 return NoHazardFound; 0
1558 ----
1559 int PreExecPos = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
1560 int PostExecPos = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
1561 ----
1562 for (auto Entry : State.DefPos) { 0
1563 int DefVALUs = Entry.second; 0
1564 if (DefVALUs != std::numeric_limits::max()) { 0
1565 if (DefVALUs >= State.ExecPos) 0
1566 PreExecPos = std::min(PreExecPos, DefVALUs); 0
1567 else if (DefVALUs < State.ExecPos) 0
1568 PostExecPos = std::min(PostExecPos, DefVALUs); 0
1569 } ----
1570 } ----
1571 ----
1572 // Need a VALUs post exec change ----
1573 if (PostExecPos == std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1574 return NoHazardFound; 0
1575 ----
1576 // Too many VALUs in intv3? ----
1577 int Intv3VALUs = PostExecPos; 0
1578 if (Intv3VALUs > Intv3MaxVALUs) 0
1579 return HazardExpired; 0
1580 ----
1581 // Too many VALUs in intv2? ----
1582 int Intv2VALUs = (State.ExecPos - PostExecPos) - 1; 0
1583 if (Intv2VALUs > Intv1plus2MaxVALUs) 0
1584 return HazardExpired; 0
1585 ----
1586 // Need a VALUs pre exec change ----
1587 if (PreExecPos == std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1588 return NoHazardFound; 0
1589 ----
1590 // Too many VALUs in intv1? ----
1591 int Intv1VALUs = PreExecPos - State.ExecPos; 0
1592 if (Intv1VALUs > Intv1plus2MaxVALUs) 0
1593 return HazardExpired; 0
1594 ----
1595 // Too many VALUs in intv1 + intv2 ----
1596 if (Intv1VALUs + Intv2VALUs > Intv1plus2MaxVALUs) 0
1597 return HazardExpired; 0
1598 ----
1599 return HazardFound; 0
1600 }; 0
1601 auto UpdateStateFn = [](StateType &State, const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1602 if (SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI)) 0
1603 State.VALUs += 1; 0
1604 }; 0
1605 ----
1606 DenseSet Visited; 0
1607 if (!hasHazard(State, IsHazardFn, UpdateStateFn, MI->getParent(), 0
1608 std::next(MI->getReverseIterator()), Visited)) 0
1609 return false; 0
1610 ----
1611 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1612 TII.get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR)) 0
1613 .addImm(0x0fff); 0
1614 ----
1615 return true; 0
1616 } 0
1617 ----
1618 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixVALUTransUseHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1619 if (!ST.hasVALUTransUseHazard()) 0
1620 return false; 0
1621 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVALU(*MI)) 0
1622 return false; 0
1623 ----
1624 SmallSet SrcVGPRs; 0
1625 ----
1626 for (const MachineOperand &Use : MI->explicit_uses()) { 0
1627 if (Use.isReg() && TRI.isVGPR(MF.getRegInfo(), Use.getReg())) 0
1628 SrcVGPRs.insert(Use.getReg()); 0
1629 } ----
1630 ----
1631 // Look for the following pattern: ----
1632 // Va <- TRANS VALU ----
1633 // intv ----
1634 // MI Va (WaitState = 0) ----
1635 // ----
1636 // Where: ----
1637 // intv <= 5 VALUs / 1 TRANS ----
1638 // ----
1639 // If found, insert an appropriate S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR before MI. ----
1640 ----
1641 const int IntvMaxVALUs = 5; 0
1642 const int IntvMaxTRANS = 1; 0
1643 ----
1644 struct StateType { ----
1645 int VALUs = 0; ----
1646 int TRANS = 0; ----
1647 }; ----
1648 ----
1649 StateType State; 0
1650 ----
1651 // This overloads expiry testing with all the hazard detection ----
1652 auto IsHazardFn = [&, this](StateType &State, const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1653 // Too many VALU states have passed ----
1654 if (State.VALUs > IntvMaxVALUs || State.TRANS > IntvMaxTRANS) 0
1655 return HazardExpired; 0
1656 ----
1657 // Instructions which cause va_vdst==0 expire hazard ----
1658 if (SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(I) || SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(I) || 0
1659 SIInstrInfo::isDS(I) || SIInstrInfo::isEXP(I) || 0
1660 (I.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR && 0
1661 I.getOperand(0).getImm() == 0x0fff)) 0
1662 return HazardExpired; 0
1663 ----
1664 // Track registers writes ----
1665 if (SIInstrInfo::isTRANS(I)) { 0
1666 for (Register Src : SrcVGPRs) { 0
1667 if (I.modifiesRegister(Src, &TRI)) { 0
1668 return HazardFound; 0
1669 } ----
1670 } 0
1671 } ----
1672 ----
1673 return NoHazardFound; 0
1674 }; 0
1675 auto UpdateStateFn = [](StateType &State, const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1676 if (SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI)) 0
1677 State.VALUs += 1; 0
1678 if (SIInstrInfo::isTRANS(MI)) 0
1679 State.TRANS += 1; 0
1680 }; 0
1681 ----
1682 DenseSet Visited; 0
1683 if (!hasHazard(State, IsHazardFn, UpdateStateFn, MI->getParent(), 0
1684 std::next(MI->getReverseIterator()), Visited)) 0
1685 return false; 0
1686 ----
1687 // Hazard is observed - insert a wait on va_dst counter to ensure hazard is ----
1688 // avoided. ----
1689 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1690 TII.get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR)) 0
1691 .addImm(AMDGPU::DepCtr::encodeFieldVaVdst(0)); 0
1692 ----
1693 return true; 0
1694 } 0
1695 ----
1696 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixWMMAHazards(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1697 if (!SIInstrInfo::isWMMA(*MI)) 0
1698 return false; 0
1699 ----
1700 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
1701 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1702 ----
1703 auto IsHazardFn = [MI, TII, TRI](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1704 if (!SIInstrInfo::isWMMA(I)) 0
1705 return false; 0
1706 ----
1707 // Src0 or Src1 of the current wmma instruction overlaps with the dest of ----
1708 // the previous wmma. ----
1709 const Register CurSrc0Reg = ----
1710 TII->getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src0)->getReg(); 0
1711 const Register CurSrc1Reg = ----
1712 TII->getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src1)->getReg(); 0
1713 ----
1714 const Register PrevDstReg = ----
1715 TII->getNamedOperand(I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst)->getReg(); 0
1716 ----
1717 if (TRI->regsOverlap(PrevDstReg, CurSrc0Reg) || 0
1718 TRI->regsOverlap(PrevDstReg, CurSrc1Reg)) { 0
1719 return true; 0
1720 } ----
1721 ----
1722 // Src2 of the current wmma instruction overlaps with the dest of the ----
1723 // previous wmma. ----
1724 const MachineOperand *Src2 = ----
1725 TII->getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src2); 0
1726 const Register CurSrc2Reg = Src2->isReg() ? Src2->getReg() : Register(); 0
1727 ----
1728 if (CurSrc2Reg != AMDGPU::NoRegister && 0
1729 TRI->regsOverlap(PrevDstReg, CurSrc2Reg)) { 0
1730 ----
1731 const MachineOperand *Src2Mods = ----
1732 TII->getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers); 0
1733 const bool NoSrc2Mods = ----
1734 (Src2Mods->getImm() & (SISrcMods::NEG | SISrcMods::NEG_HI)) == 0; 0
1735 // Exception: there is no hazard if the wmma instructions are of the same ----
1736 // type and there is no input modifier on src2 of the current instruction. ----
1737 return !(NoSrc2Mods && (TII->pseudoToMCOpcode(I.getOpcode()) == 0
1738 TII->pseudoToMCOpcode(MI->getOpcode()))); 0
1739 } ----
1740 ----
1741 return false; 0
1742 }; 0
1743 ----
1744 auto IsExpiredFn = [](const MachineInstr &I, int) { 0
1745 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(I); 0
1746 }; ----
1747 ----
1748 if (::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn) == 0
1749 std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1750 return false; 0
1751 ----
1752 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(AMDGPU::V_NOP_e32)); 0
1753 ----
1754 return true; 0
1755 } ----
1756 ----
1757 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixShift64HighRegBug(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1758 if (!ST.hasShift64HighRegBug()) 0
1759 return false; 0
1760 ----
1761 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
1762 default: 0
1763 return false; 0
1764 case AMDGPU::V_LSHLREV_B64_e64: 0
1765 case AMDGPU::V_LSHRREV_B64_e64: ----
1766 case AMDGPU::V_ASHRREV_I64_e64: ----
1767 break; 0
1768 } ----
1769 ----
1770 MachineOperand *Amt = TII.getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src0); 0
1771 if (!Amt->isReg()) 0
1772 return false; 0
1773 ----
1774 Register AmtReg = Amt->getReg(); 0
1775 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1776 // Check if this is a last VGPR in the allocation block. ----
1777 if (!TRI.isVGPR(MRI, AmtReg) || ((AmtReg - AMDGPU::VGPR0) & 7) != 7) 0
1778 return false; 0
1779 ----
1780 if (AmtReg != AMDGPU::VGPR255 && MRI.isPhysRegUsed(AmtReg + 1)) 0
1781 return false; 0
1782 ----
1783 MachineOperand *Src1 = TII.getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src1); 0
1784 bool OverlappedSrc = Src1->isReg() && TRI.regsOverlap(Src1->getReg(), AmtReg); 0
1785 bool OverlappedDst = MI->modifiesRegister(AmtReg, &TRI); 0
1786 bool Overlapped = OverlappedSrc || OverlappedDst; 0
1787 ----
1788 assert(!OverlappedDst || !OverlappedSrc || 0
1789 Src1->getReg() == MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); ----
1790 assert(ST.needsAlignedVGPRs()); 0
1791 static_assert(AMDGPU::VGPR0 + 1 == AMDGPU::VGPR1); ----
1792 ----
1793 Register NewReg; 0
1794 for (MCRegister Reg : Overlapped ? AMDGPU::VReg_64_Align2RegClass 0
1795 : AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass) { 0
1796 if (!MI->modifiesRegister(Reg, &TRI) && !MI->readsRegister(Reg, &TRI)) { 0
1797 NewReg = Reg; 0
1798 break; 0
1799 } ----
1800 } ----
1801 ----
1802 Register NewAmt = Overlapped ? (Register)TRI.getSubReg(NewReg, AMDGPU::sub1) 0
1803 : NewReg; 0
1804 Register NewAmtLo; 0
1805 ----
1806 if (Overlapped) 0
1807 NewAmtLo = TRI.getSubReg(NewReg, AMDGPU::sub0); 0
1808 ----
1809 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1810 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
1811 // Insert a full wait count because found register might be pending a wait. ----
1812 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT)) 0
1813 .addImm(0); 0
1814 ----
1815 // Insert V_SWAP_B32 instruction(s) and run hazard recognizer on them. ----
1816 if (Overlapped) 0
1817 runOnInstruction( 0
1818 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_SWAP_B32), NewAmtLo) 0
1819 .addDef(AmtReg - 1) 0
1820 .addReg(AmtReg - 1, RegState::Undef) 0
1821 .addReg(NewAmtLo, RegState::Undef)); 0
1822 runOnInstruction(BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_SWAP_B32), NewAmt) 0
1823 .addDef(AmtReg) 0
1824 .addReg(AmtReg, RegState::Undef) 0
1825 .addReg(NewAmt, RegState::Undef)); 0
1826 ----
1827 // Instructions emitted after the current instruction will be processed by the ----
1828 // parent loop of the hazard recognizer in a natural way. ----
1829 BuildMI(*MBB, std::next(MI->getIterator()), DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_SWAP_B32), 0
1830 AmtReg) ----
1831 .addDef(NewAmt) 0
1832 .addReg(NewAmt) 0
1833 .addReg(AmtReg); 0
1834 if (Overlapped) 0
1835 BuildMI(*MBB, std::next(MI->getIterator()), DL, TII.get(AMDGPU::V_SWAP_B32), 0
1836 AmtReg - 1) 0
1837 .addDef(NewAmtLo) 0
1838 .addReg(NewAmtLo) 0
1839 .addReg(AmtReg - 1); 0
1840 ----
1841 // Re-running hazard recognizer on the modified instruction is not necessary, ----
1842 // inserted V_SWAP_B32 has already both read and write new registers so ----
1843 // hazards related to these register has already been handled. ----
1844 Amt->setReg(NewAmt); 0
1845 Amt->setIsKill(false); 0
1846 // We do not update liveness, so verifier may see it as undef. ----
1847 Amt->setIsUndef(); 0
1848 if (OverlappedDst) 0
1849 MI->getOperand(0).setReg(NewReg); 0
1850 if (OverlappedSrc) { 0
1851 Src1->setReg(NewReg); 0
1852 Src1->setIsKill(false); 0
1853 Src1->setIsUndef(); 0
1854 } ----
1855 ----
1856 return true; 0
1857 } ----
1858 ----
1859 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkNSAtoVMEMHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1860 int NSAtoVMEMWaitStates = 1; 0
1861 ----
1862 if (!ST.hasNSAtoVMEMBug()) 0
1863 return 0; 0
1864 ----
1865 if (!SIInstrInfo::isMUBUF(*MI) && !SIInstrInfo::isMTBUF(*MI)) 0
1866 return 0; 0
1867 ----
1868 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
1869 const auto *Offset = TII->getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::offset); 0
1870 if (!Offset || (Offset->getImm() & 6) == 0) 0
1871 return 0; 0
1872 ----
1873 auto IsHazardFn = [TII](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1874 if (!SIInstrInfo::isMIMG(I)) 0
1875 return false; 0
1876 const AMDGPU::MIMGInfo *Info = AMDGPU::getMIMGInfo(I.getOpcode()); 0
1877 return Info->MIMGEncoding == AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx10NSA && 0
1878 TII->getInstSizeInBytes(I) >= 16; 0
1879 }; 0
1880 ----
1881 return NSAtoVMEMWaitStates - getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, 1); 0
1882 } ----
1883 ----
1884 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkFPAtomicToDenormModeHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1885 int FPAtomicToDenormModeWaitStates = 3; 0
1886 ----
1887 if (!ST.hasFPAtomicToDenormModeHazard()) 0
1888 return 0; 0
1889 ----
1890 if (MI->getOpcode() != AMDGPU::S_DENORM_MODE) 0
1891 return 0; 0
1892 ----
1893 auto IsHazardFn = [](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
1894 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVMEM(I) && !SIInstrInfo::isFLAT(I)) 0
1895 return false; 0
1896 return SIInstrInfo::isFPAtomic(I); 0
1897 }; ----
1898 ----
1899 auto IsExpiredFn = [](const MachineInstr &MI, int WaitStates) { 0
1900 if (WaitStates >= 3 || SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI)) 0
1901 return true; 0
1902 ----
1903 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
1904 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT: 0
1905 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_VSCNT: ----
1906 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_VMCNT: ----
1907 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_EXPCNT: ----
1908 case AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_LGKMCNT: ----
1909 case AMDGPU::S_WAIT_IDLE: ----
1910 return true; 0
1911 default: 0
1912 break; 0
1913 } ----
1914 ----
1915 return false; 0
1916 }; ----
1917 ----
1918 return FPAtomicToDenormModeWaitStates - ----
1919 ::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn); 0
1920 } ----

1927 ----
1928 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkMFMAPadding(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1929 // Early exit if no padding is requested. ----
1930 if (MFMAPaddingRatio == 0) 0
1931 return 0; 0
1932 ----
1933 const SIMachineFunctionInfo *MFI = MF.getInfo(); 0
1934 if (!SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(*MI) || MFI->getOccupancy() < 2) 0
1935 return 0; 0
1936 ----
1937 int NeighborMFMALatency = 0; 0
1938 auto IsNeighboringMFMA = [&NeighborMFMALatency, 0
1939 this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1940 if (!SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(MI)) 0
1941 return false; 0
1942 ----
1943 NeighborMFMALatency = this->getMFMAPipelineWaitStates(MI); 0
1944 return true; 0
1945 }; 0
1946 ----
1947 const int MaxMFMAPipelineWaitStates = 16; 0
1948 int WaitStatesSinceNeighborMFMA = ----
1949 getWaitStatesSince(IsNeighboringMFMA, MaxMFMAPipelineWaitStates); 0
1950 ----
1951 int NeighborMFMAPaddingNeeded = ----
1952 (NeighborMFMALatency * MFMAPaddingRatio / 100) - 0
1953 WaitStatesSinceNeighborMFMA; 0
1954 ----
1955 return std::max(0, NeighborMFMAPaddingNeeded); 0
1956 } ----
1957 ----
1958 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkMAIHazards908(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1959 int WaitStatesNeeded = 0; 0
1960 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1961 ----
1962 auto IsVALUFn = [](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1963 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI) || MI.isInlineAsm(); 0
1964 }; ----
1965 ----
1966 if (Opc != AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_READ_B32_e64) { // MFMA or v_accvgpr_write 0
1967 const int LegacyVALUWritesVGPRWaitStates = 2; 0
1968 const int VALUWritesExecWaitStates = 4; 0
1969 const int MaxWaitStates = 4; 0
1970 ----
1971 int WaitStatesNeededForUse = VALUWritesExecWaitStates - 0
1972 getWaitStatesSinceDef(AMDGPU::EXEC, IsVALUFn, MaxWaitStates); 0
1973 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
1974 ----
1975 if (WaitStatesNeeded < MaxWaitStates) { 0
1976 for (const MachineOperand &Use : MI->explicit_uses()) { 0
1977 const int MaxWaitStates = 2; 0
1978 ----
1979 if (!Use.isReg() || !TRI.isVGPR(MF.getRegInfo(), Use.getReg())) 0
1980 continue; 0
1981 ----
1982 int WaitStatesNeededForUse = LegacyVALUWritesVGPRWaitStates - 0
1983 getWaitStatesSinceDef(Use.getReg(), IsVALUFn, MaxWaitStates); 0
1984 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
1985 ----
1986 if (WaitStatesNeeded == MaxWaitStates) 0
1987 break; 0
1988 } ----
1989 } ----
1990 } ----
1991 ----
1992 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->explicit_operands()) { 0
1993 if (!Op.isReg() || !TRI.isAGPR(MF.getRegInfo(), Op.getReg())) 0
1994 continue; 0
1995 ----
1996 if (Op.isDef() && Opc != AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_WRITE_B32_e64) 0
1997 continue; 0
1998 ----
1999 const int MFMAWritesAGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 4; 0
2000 const int MFMAWritesAGPROverlappedSrcCWaitStates = 2; 0
2001 const int MFMA4x4WritesAGPRAccVgprReadWaitStates = 4; 0
2002 const int MFMA16x16WritesAGPRAccVgprReadWaitStates = 10; 0
2003 const int MFMA32x32WritesAGPRAccVgprReadWaitStates = 18; 0
2004 const int MFMA4x4WritesAGPRAccVgprWriteWaitStates = 1; 0
2005 const int MFMA16x16WritesAGPRAccVgprWriteWaitStates = 7; 0
2006 const int MFMA32x32WritesAGPRAccVgprWriteWaitStates = 15; 0
2007 const int MaxWaitStates = 18; 0
2008 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
2009 unsigned HazardDefLatency = 0; 0
2010 ----
2011 auto IsOverlappedMFMAFn = [Reg, &HazardDefLatency, 0
2012 this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2013 if (!SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(MI)) 0
2014 return false; 0
2015 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2016 if (DstReg == Reg) 0
2017 return false; 0
2018 HazardDefLatency = 0
2019 std::max(HazardDefLatency, TSchedModel.computeInstrLatency(&MI)); 0
2020 return TRI.regsOverlap(DstReg, Reg); 0
2021 }; 0
2022 ----
2023 int WaitStatesSinceDef = getWaitStatesSinceDef(Reg, IsOverlappedMFMAFn, 0
2024 MaxWaitStates); ----
2025 int NeedWaitStates = MFMAWritesAGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates; 0
2026 int SrcCIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src2); 0
2027 int OpNo = Op.getOperandNo(); 0
2028 if (OpNo == SrcCIdx) { 0
2029 NeedWaitStates = MFMAWritesAGPROverlappedSrcCWaitStates; 0
2030 } else if (Opc == AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_READ_B32_e64) { 0
2031 switch (HazardDefLatency) { 0
2032 case 2: NeedWaitStates = MFMA4x4WritesAGPRAccVgprReadWaitStates; 0
2033 break; 0
2034 case 8: NeedWaitStates = MFMA16x16WritesAGPRAccVgprReadWaitStates; 0
2035 break; 0
2036 case 16: [[fallthrough]]; 0
2037 default: NeedWaitStates = MFMA32x32WritesAGPRAccVgprReadWaitStates; 0
2038 break; 0
2039 } ----
2040 } else if (Opc == AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_WRITE_B32_e64) { 0
2041 switch (HazardDefLatency) { 0
2042 case 2: NeedWaitStates = MFMA4x4WritesAGPRAccVgprWriteWaitStates; 0
2043 break; 0
2044 case 8: NeedWaitStates = MFMA16x16WritesAGPRAccVgprWriteWaitStates; 0
2045 break; 0
2046 case 16: [[fallthrough]]; 0
2047 default: NeedWaitStates = MFMA32x32WritesAGPRAccVgprWriteWaitStates; 0
2048 break; 0
2049 } ----
2050 } ----
2051 ----
2052 int WaitStatesNeededForUse = NeedWaitStates - WaitStatesSinceDef; 0
2053 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
2054 ----
2055 if (WaitStatesNeeded == MaxWaitStates) 0
2056 return WaitStatesNeeded; // Early exit. 0
2057 ----
2058 auto IsAccVgprWriteFn = [Reg, this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2059 if (MI.getOpcode() != AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_WRITE_B32_e64) 0
2060 return false; 0
2061 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2062 return TRI.regsOverlap(Reg, DstReg); 0
2063 }; 0
2064 ----
2065 const int AccVGPRWriteMFMAReadSrcCWaitStates = 1; 0
2066 const int AccVGPRWriteMFMAReadSrcABWaitStates = 3; 0
2067 const int AccVGPRWriteAccVgprReadWaitStates = 3; 0
2068 NeedWaitStates = AccVGPRWriteMFMAReadSrcABWaitStates; 0
2069 if (OpNo == SrcCIdx) 0
2070 NeedWaitStates = AccVGPRWriteMFMAReadSrcCWaitStates; 0
2071 else if (Opc == AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_READ_B32_e64) 0
2072 NeedWaitStates = AccVGPRWriteAccVgprReadWaitStates; 0
2073 ----
2074 WaitStatesNeededForUse = NeedWaitStates - 0
2075 getWaitStatesSinceDef(Reg, IsAccVgprWriteFn, MaxWaitStates); 0
2076 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
2077 ----
2078 if (WaitStatesNeeded == MaxWaitStates) 0
2079 return WaitStatesNeeded; // Early exit. 0
2080 } ----
2081 ----
2082 if (Opc == AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_WRITE_B32_e64) { 0
2083 const int MFMA4x4ReadSrcCAccVgprWriteWaitStates = 0; 0
2084 const int MFMA16x16ReadSrcCAccVgprWriteWaitStates = 5; 0
2085 const int MFMA32x32ReadSrcCAccVgprWriteWaitStates = 13; 0
2086 const int MaxWaitStates = 13; 0
2087 Register DstReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2088 unsigned HazardDefLatency = 0; 0
2089 ----
2090 auto IsSrcCMFMAFn = [DstReg, &HazardDefLatency, 0
2091 this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2092 if (!SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(MI)) 0
2093 return false; 0
2094 Register Reg = TII.getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src2)->getReg(); 0
2095 HazardDefLatency = 0
2096 std::max(HazardDefLatency, TSchedModel.computeInstrLatency(&MI)); 0
2097 return TRI.regsOverlap(Reg, DstReg); 0
2098 }; 0
2099 ----
2100 int WaitStatesSince = getWaitStatesSince(IsSrcCMFMAFn, MaxWaitStates); 0
2101 int NeedWaitStates; ----
2102 switch (HazardDefLatency) { 0
2103 case 2: NeedWaitStates = MFMA4x4ReadSrcCAccVgprWriteWaitStates; 0
2104 break; 0
2105 case 8: NeedWaitStates = MFMA16x16ReadSrcCAccVgprWriteWaitStates; 0
2106 break; 0
2107 case 16: [[fallthrough]]; 0
2108 default: NeedWaitStates = MFMA32x32ReadSrcCAccVgprWriteWaitStates; 0
2109 break; 0
2110 } ----
2111 ----
2112 int WaitStatesNeededForUse = NeedWaitStates - WaitStatesSince; 0
2113 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
2114 } ----
2115 ----
2116 // Pad neighboring MFMA with noops for better inter-wave performance. ----
2117 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, checkMFMAPadding(MI)); 0
2118 ----
2119 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
2120 } ----

2122 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkMAIHazards90A(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
2123 int WaitStatesNeeded = 0; 0
2124 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2125 ----
2126 auto IsLegacyVALUFn = [](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2127 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI) && !SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(MI); 0
2128 }; ----
2129 ----
2130 auto IsLegacyVALUNotDotFn = [](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2131 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI) && !SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(MI) && 0
2132 !SIInstrInfo::isDOT(MI); 0

2134 ----

2160 const int SMFMA16x16WritesVGPROverlappedDMFMASrcCWaitStates = 9; 0
2161 const int SMFMA32x32WritesVGPROverlappedDMFMASrcCWaitStates = 17; 0
2162 const int DMFMA16x16WritesVGPROverlappedSrcCWaitStates = 9; 0
2163 const int DMFMA4x4WritesVGPROverlappedSrcCWaitStates = 4; 0
2164 const int SMFMA4x4WritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 5; 0
2165 const int SMFMA16x16WritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 11; 0
2166 const int SMFMA32x32WritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 19; 0

2169 const int GFX940_SMFMA8PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 10; 0

2171 const int GFX940_XDL2PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 5; 0
2172 const int GFX940_XDL4PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 7; 0
2173 const int GFX940_XDL8PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 11; 0
2174 const int GFX940_XDL16PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates = 19; 0

2181 if (!Use.isReg()) 0

2183 Register Reg = Use.getReg(); 0
2184 bool FullReg; ----

2186 ----

2188 this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2189 if (!SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(MI)) 0
2190 return false; 0
2191 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2192 FullReg = (DstReg == Reg); 0
2193 MI1 = &MI; 0
2194 return TRI.regsOverlap(DstReg, Reg); 0

2200 ----
2201 int NumWaitStates = ----
2202 getWaitStatesSinceDef(Reg, IsOverlappedMFMAFn, MaxWaitStates); 0
2203 if (NumWaitStates == std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
2204 continue; 0
2205 ----
2206 int OpNo = Use.getOperandNo(); 0
2207 unsigned Opc1 = MI1->getOpcode(); 0
2208 int NeedWaitStates = 0; 0
2209 if (OpNo == SrcCIdx) { 0
2210 if (!isDGEMM(Opc) && (!ST.hasGFX940Insts() && isDGEMM(Opc1))) { 0
2211 NeedWaitStates = 0; 0

2218 else if (ST.hasGFX940Insts() && 0
2219 TSchedModel.computeInstrLatency(MI1) == 2) 0
2220 NeedWaitStates = GFX940_SMFMA4x4WritesVGPRFullSrcCWaitStates; 0
2221 } else { ----
2222 switch (Opc1) { 0
2223 case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_16X16X4F64_e64: 0

2229 break; 0

2232 if (!isXDL(ST, *MI)) 0

2235 default: 0
2236 if (ST.hasGFX940Insts() && isXDL(ST, *MI) && !isXDL(ST, *MI1)) 0
2237 break; 0
2238 switch (TSchedModel.computeInstrLatency(MI1)) { 0
2239 case 2: 0
2240 NeedWaitStates = ST.hasGFX940Insts() 0
2241 ? isXDL(ST, *MI1) 0
2242 ? GFX940_XDL2PassWritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates ----
2243 : SMFMA4x4WritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates ----

2247 break; 0
2248 case 4: 0
2249 assert(ST.hasGFX940Insts()); 0
2250 NeedWaitStates = isXDL(ST, *MI1) 0
2251 ? GFX940_XDL4PassWritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates 0
2252 : GFX940_SMFMA4PassWritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates; ----
2253 break; 0
2254 case 8: 0
2255 NeedWaitStates = ST.hasGFX940Insts() 0
2256 ? isXDL(ST, *MI1) 0
2257 ? GFX940_XDL8PassWritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates ----
2258 : GFX940_SMFMA8PassWritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates ----

2260 ? SMFMA16x16WritesVGPROverlappedDMFMASrcCWaitStates ----
2261 : SMFMA16x16WritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates; ----
2262 break; 0
2263 case 16: [[fallthrough]]; 0
2264 default: ----
2265 NeedWaitStates = ST.hasGFX940Insts() 0
2266 ? isXDL(ST, *MI1) 0
2267 ? GFX940_XDL16PassWritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates ----
2268 : GFX940_SMFMA16PassWritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates ----
2269 : isDGEMM(Opc) 0
2270 ? SMFMA32x32WritesVGPROverlappedDMFMASrcCWaitStates ----
2271 : SMFMA32x32WritesVGPROverlappedSMFMASrcCWaitStates; ----
2272 } ----
2273 } ----
2274 } ----
2275 } else { ----
2276 switch (Opc1) { 0
2277 case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_16X16X4F64_e64: 0
2278 case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_16X16X4F64_vgprcd_e64: ----

2280 case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_16X16X4F64_mac_vgprcd_e64: ----
2281 NeedWaitStates = DMFMA16x16WritesVGPROverlappedMFMASrcABWaitStates; 0
2282 break; 0
2283 case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_4X4X4F64_e64: 0

2285 NeedWaitStates = DMFMA4x4WritesVGPROverlappedMFMASrcABWaitStates; 0
2286 break; 0
2287 default: 0
2288 switch (TSchedModel.computeInstrLatency(MI1)) { 0
2289 case 2: 0
2290 NeedWaitStates = ST.hasGFX940Insts() 0
2291 ? isXDL(ST, *MI1) 0
2292 ? GFX940_XDL2PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates ----
2293 : GFX940_SMFMA2PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates ----
2294 : SMFMA4x4WritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates; ----
2295 break; 0
2296 case 4: 0
2297 assert(ST.hasGFX940Insts()); 0
2298 NeedWaitStates = isXDL(ST, *MI1) 0
2299 ? GFX940_XDL4PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates 0
2300 : GFX940_SMFMA4PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates; ----
2301 break; 0
2302 case 8: 0
2303 NeedWaitStates = ST.hasGFX940Insts() 0
2304 ? isXDL(ST, *MI1) 0
2305 ? GFX940_XDL8PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates ----
2306 : GFX940_SMFMA8PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates ----
2307 : SMFMA16x16WritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates; ----
2308 break; 0
2309 case 16: [[fallthrough]]; 0
2310 default: ----
2311 NeedWaitStates = ST.hasGFX940Insts() 0
2312 ? isXDL(ST, *MI1) 0
2313 ? GFX940_XDL16PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates ----
2314 : GFX940_SMFMA16PassWritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates ----
2315 : SMFMA32x32WritesVGPROverlappedSrcABWaitStates; ----
2316 } ----
2317 } ----
2318 } ----
2319 if (WaitStatesNeeded >= NeedWaitStates) 0
2320 continue; 0
2321 ----
2322 WaitStatesNeededForUse = NeedWaitStates - NumWaitStates; 0
2323 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0
2324 ----
2325 if (WaitStatesNeeded == MaxWaitStates) 0
2326 break; 0
2327 } ----
2328 ----
2329 return WaitStatesNeeded; 0
2330 } ----

2332 int GCNHazardRecognizer::checkMAILdStHazards(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
2333 // On gfx90a+ relevant hazards are checked in checkMAIVALUHazards() ----
2334 if (!ST.hasMAIInsts() || ST.hasGFX90AInsts()) 0
2335 return 0; 0
2336 ----
2337 int WaitStatesNeeded = 0; 0
2338 ----
2339 auto IsAccVgprReadFn = [](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2340 return MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_READ_B32_e64; 0
2341 }; ----
2342 ----
2343 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->explicit_uses()) { 0
2344 if (!Op.isReg() || !TRI.isVGPR(MF.getRegInfo(), Op.getReg())) 0
2345 continue; 0
2346 ----
2347 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
2348 ----
2349 const int AccVgprReadLdStWaitStates = 2; 0

2356 ----
2357 if (WaitStatesNeeded == MaxWaitStates) 0

2362 MI.getOpcode() != AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_WRITE_B32_e64) 0
2363 return false; 0

2365 return SIInstrInfo::isVALU(MI) && !SIInstrInfo::isMAI(MI); 0
2366 }; ----
2367 return getWaitStatesSinceDef(Reg, IsVALUFn, 2 /*MaxWaitStates*/) < 0
2368 std::numeric_limits::max(); 0

2371 WaitStatesNeededForUse = VALUWriteAccVgprRdWrLdStDepVALUWaitStates - 0
2372 getWaitStatesSince(IsVALUAccVgprRdWrCheckFn, MaxWaitStates); 0
2373 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0

2375 ----

2625 case 16: [[fallthrough]]; 0

2629 : ST.hasGFX940Insts() 0

2638 WaitStatesNeeded = std::max(WaitStatesNeeded, WaitStatesNeededForUse); 0

2640 if (WaitStatesNeeded == MaxWaitStates) 0
2641 break; 0
2642 } ----

2644 auto IsSMFMAReadAsCFn = [&Reg, &MFMA, this](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2645 if (!SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(MI) || isDGEMM(MI.getOpcode()) || 0

2689 ----
2690 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::ShouldPreferAnother(SUnit *SU) { 0
2691 if (!SU->isInstr()) 0
2692 return false; 0
2693 ----
2694 const MachineInstr *MAI = nullptr; 0
2695 ----
2696 auto IsMFMAFn = [&MAI](const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2697 MAI = nullptr; 0
2698 if (SIInstrInfo::isMFMA(MI)) 0
2699 MAI = &MI; 0
2700 return MAI != nullptr; 0
2701 }; 0
2702 ----
2703 MachineInstr *MI = SU->getInstr(); 0
2704 if (IsMFMAFn(*MI)) { 0
2705 int W = getWaitStatesSince(IsMFMAFn, 16); 0
2706 if (MAI) 0
2707 return W < (int)TSchedModel.computeInstrLatency(MAI); 0
2708 } ----
2709 ----
2710 return false; 0
2711 } ----
2712 ----
2713 bool GCNHazardRecognizer::fixVALUMaskWriteHazard(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
2714 if (!ST.isWave64()) 0
2715 return false; 0
2716 if (!ST.hasVALUMaskWriteHazard()) 0
2717 return false; 0
2718 if (!SIInstrInfo::isSALU(*MI)) 0
2719 return false; 0
2720 ----
2721 // The hazard sequence is three instructions: ----
2722 // 1. VALU reads SGPR as mask ----
2723 // 2. SALU writes SGPR ----
2724 // 3. SALU reads SGPR ----
2725 // The hazard can expire if the distance between 2 and 3 is sufficient. ----
2726 // In practice this happens <10% of the time, hence this always assumes ----
2727 // the hazard exists if 1 and 2 are present to avoid searching. ----
2728 ----
2729 const MachineOperand *SDSTOp = TII.getNamedOperand(*MI, AMDGPU::OpName::sdst); 0
2730 if (!SDSTOp || !SDSTOp->isReg()) 0
2731 return false; 0
2732 ----
2733 const Register HazardReg = SDSTOp->getReg(); 0
2734 if (HazardReg == AMDGPU::EXEC || 0
2735 HazardReg == AMDGPU::EXEC_LO || 0
2736 HazardReg == AMDGPU::EXEC_HI || 0
2737 HazardReg == AMDGPU::M0) 0
2738 return false; 0
2739 ----
2740 auto IsHazardFn = [HazardReg, this](const MachineInstr &I) { 0
2741 switch (I.getOpcode()) { 0
2742 case AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e32: 0
2743 case AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_dpp: ----
2744 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B16_e32: ----
2745 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B16_dpp: ----
2746 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B32_e32: ----
2747 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B32_dpp: ----
2748 case AMDGPU::V_DIV_FMAS_F32_e64: ----
2749 case AMDGPU::V_DIV_FMAS_F64_e64: ----
2750 case AMDGPU::V_SUBB_U32_e32: ----
2751 case AMDGPU::V_SUBB_U32_dpp: ----
2752 case AMDGPU::V_SUBBREV_U32_e32: ----
2753 case AMDGPU::V_SUBBREV_U32_dpp: ----
2754 // These implicitly read VCC as mask source. ----
2755 return HazardReg == AMDGPU::VCC || 0
2756 HazardReg == AMDGPU::VCC_LO || 0
2757 HazardReg == AMDGPU::VCC_HI; 0
2758 case AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e64: 0
2759 case AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e64_dpp: ----
2760 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B16_e64: ----
2761 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B16_e64_dpp: ----
2762 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B32_e64: ----
2763 case AMDGPU::V_CNDMASK_B32_e64_dpp: ----
2764 case AMDGPU::V_SUBB_U32_e64: ----
2765 case AMDGPU::V_SUBB_U32_e64_dpp: ----
2766 case AMDGPU::V_SUBBREV_U32_e64: ----
2767 case AMDGPU::V_SUBBREV_U32_e64_dpp: { ----
2768 // Only check mask register overlaps. ----
2769 const MachineOperand *SSRCOp = TII.getNamedOperand(I, AMDGPU::OpName::src2); 0
2770 assert(SSRCOp); 0
2771 return TRI.regsOverlap(SSRCOp->getReg(), HazardReg); 0
2772 } ----
2773 default: 0
2774 return false; 0
2775 } ----
2776 }; 0
2777 ----
2778 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
2779 auto IsExpiredFn = [&MRI, this](const MachineInstr &I, int) { 0
2780 // s_waitcnt_depctr sa_sdst(0) mitigates hazard. ----
2781 if (I.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR && 0
2782 AMDGPU::DepCtr::decodeFieldSaSdst(I.getOperand(0).getImm()) == 0) 0
2783 return true; 0
2784 ----
2785 // VALU access to any SGPR or literal constant other than HazardReg ----
2786 // mitigates hazard. No need to check HazardReg here as this will ----
2787 // only be called when !IsHazardFn. ----
2788 if (!SIInstrInfo::isVALU(I)) 0
2789 return false; 0
2790 for (int OpNo = 0, End = I.getNumOperands(); OpNo < End; ++OpNo) { 0
2791 const MachineOperand &Op = I.getOperand(OpNo); 0
2792 if (Op.isReg()) { 0
2793 Register OpReg = Op.getReg(); 0
2794 // Only consider uses ----
2795 if (!Op.isUse()) 0
2796 continue; 0
2797 // Ignore EXEC ----
2798 if (OpReg == AMDGPU::EXEC || 0
2799 OpReg == AMDGPU::EXEC_LO || 0
2800 OpReg == AMDGPU::EXEC_HI) 0
2801 continue; 0
2802 // Ignore all implicit uses except VCC ----
2803 if (Op.isImplicit()) { 0
2804 if (OpReg == AMDGPU::VCC || 0
2805 OpReg == AMDGPU::VCC_LO || 0
2806 OpReg == AMDGPU::VCC_HI) 0
2807 return true; 0
2808 continue; 0
2809 } ----
2810 if (TRI.isSGPRReg(MRI, OpReg)) 0
2811 return true; 0
2812 } else { ----
2813 const MCInstrDesc &InstDesc = I.getDesc(); 0
2814 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo = InstDesc.operands()[OpNo]; 0
2815 if (!TII.isInlineConstant(Op, OpInfo)) 0
2816 return true; 0
2817 } ----
2818 } ----
2819 return false; 0
2820 }; 0
2821 ----
2822 // Check for hazard ----
2823 if (::getWaitStatesSince(IsHazardFn, MI, IsExpiredFn) == 0
2824 std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
2825 return false; 0
2826 ----
2827 auto NextMI = std::next(MI->getIterator()); 0
2828 ----
2829 // Add s_waitcnt_depctr sa_sdst(0) after SALU write. ----
2830 BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), NextMI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
2831 TII.get(AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_DEPCTR)) 0
2832 .addImm(AMDGPU::DepCtr::encodeFieldSaSdst(0)); 0
2833 ----
2834 // SALU write may be s_getpc in a bundle. ----
2835 if (MI->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_GETPC_B64) { 0
2836 // Update offsets of any references in the bundle. ----
2837 while (NextMI != MI->getParent()->end() && 0
2838 NextMI->isBundledWithPred()) { 0
2839 for (auto &Operand : NextMI->operands()) { 0
2840 if (Operand.isGlobal()) 0
2841 Operand.setOffset(Operand.getOffset() + 4); 0
2842 } ----
2843 NextMI++; 0
2844 } ----
2845 } ----
2846 ----
2847 return true; 0
2848 } ----
